lzh_formatted:
  title: 無題
  author: 安應世
  language: lzh
  text: 雨濕雲蒸暗海城。傷心前歲送郞行。燕鴻寂寞音書斷。深院無人杏子成。
korean:
  title: 무제
  author: 안응세
  language: kor
  text: |-
    비 젖고 구름쪄서 바닷성이 어두울 제
    마음 슬퍼라 지난 해에 임을 보내었소
    제비랑 기러기랑 적막하여 소식마저 끊이고는
    사람 없는 깊은 원에 살구만 맺혔어라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0350&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Untitled
  author: An Eung-se
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Rain soaks the city by the sea as clouds drift thick and dim.
    My heart aches—last year I watched my love depart.
    Swallows and geese in solitude, their messages no longer come,
    While in the empty courtyard, apricots ripen unwatched, alone.
  footnotes:
    - The swallows and geese (yanghong) traditionally carry letters and tidings between distant lovers in East Asian poetry.
    - The ripening apricots in the deserted courtyard suggest the passage of seasons and the poet's loneliness, as spring turns to summer without the beloved's return.
